Project name: Waltle
Created for: JumboHack 2025 under the "Down the Rabbit Hole" track

Goals: Develop a Disney-inspired version of Wordle run in terminal using C++. 
We wanted to make the game easy to follow, visually appealing, with diverse 
functionality.

Members:
Neil Kenney - Design the front and backend of game, manage team, and build
program
Michael Bachman - Help with concept and creative development
Brandon Huang - Debugging, testing, optimizing code

Acknowledgement: All hints were generated using ChatGPT. Some small pieces of
code were generated using ChatGPT, including random number generation and ANSI
escape codes for different colors.